Title:     75 hot word processing tips.
             (includes related article about five universal word
             processing tips)
Author:    Campbell, George


Abstract:  Seventy-five tips for using popular word processing programs
           are presented. Tips are from contributors, companies and
           readers. Various topics are covered such as how to format a
           block of text, how to insert currency symbolism and how to
           place sections of 'boilerplate' into a document. Readers are
           advised to look at tips for programs other than the ones they
           use because their own programs probably incorporate similar
           capabilities. Programs covered include: WordPerfect 5.1 for
           Windows; Microsoft Word for Windows 2.0; Microsoft Word for
           DOS; Ami Pro 2.0 and 3.0.; and WordStar for DOS and Windows.
           Some tips are universal. They apply regardless of the
           particular program being used.
